        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
          <p>Spain is in the Central European Time Zone (UTC+1:00).  When it is 1pm in NY it is 7pm in Spain.</p>
          <p>Shops are usually open from 9:30am until 1:30pm and 4:30pm to 8:00pm.  Traditionally they close at lunch times.  Meals are usually eaten around 9-10am, 2-3pm and 9-10pm.  Most shops are also closed on Sundays.</p>
          <p>In late August and early September La Coruña is generally around the mid to high 70’s during the day and the low 60’s at night.  Short rain showers may occur but are more unlikely during this time of year.</p>
          <p>Within the city of La Coruña there are taxi stands near the Plaza de Maria Pita and the Plaza de Ourense.  Taxis are generally white.  You can also call a taxi for pickup.</p>
          <p>Radiotaxi: +34 981 243 333</p>
          <p>Teletaxi: +34 981 287 777</p>
          <br>
          <p>Country code: +34</p>
          <p>Area Code for La Coruña: 981</p>
          <br>
          <p>Electricity: 220V/50 Hz</p>
          <p>You will need an adapter to use the electrical outlets in Spain.</p>
        </div>
